    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/7–2744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-27">July 27,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received July 28—1:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5986. From Pell. War Crimes Commission Publicity Committee met July 26. Will make
                    statement on work of Commission including section on powers of Commission and
                    specific statement that so far it has not been authorized to consider offenses
                    committed in Axis territory against Axis nationals because of race, creed or
                    politics.</p>
                <p>Czechoslovakia representative will announce his Government’s support on granting
                    such powers. I understand United States Government will not object to such
                    extension of powers. I shall certainly be asked questions at press conference
                    Thursday August 3, 11 a.m. Please send official statement. [Pell.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
